<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="596" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,545,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,617,642]" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Etymology</emphasis>
. From Latin 
<emphasis box="[473,546,618,641]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">aurum</emphasis>
= gold and 
<emphasis box="[679,806,617,642]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">caudatus =</emphasis>
tail, appendage and refers to the yellowish coloration of the apex of abdomen of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="596" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,545,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,689,714]" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Compound eye yellowish, with brown spots (
<figureCitation box="[852,989,689,714]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1963,1985]" captionTargetBox="[200,1390,208,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[200,1394,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head and tegminae of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. A) holotype head, dorsal view; B) paratype head, lateral view; C) holotype tegminae, dorsolateral view;D) idem." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171542/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 2A–B</figureCitation>
). Tegmina with yellowish spot at basal third, from anal margin towards shoulder of costal margin (
<figureCitation box="[816,952,725,750]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1963,1985]" captionTargetBox="[200,1390,208,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[200,1394,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head and tegminae of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. A) holotype head, dorsal view; B) paratype head, lateral view; C) holotype tegminae, dorsolateral view;D) idem." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171542/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 2C–D</figureCitation>
). Abdominal segment 8–11 yellowish (Fig. 
<figureCitation box="[151,288,761,786]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,418,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,411,1850]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Isagoras aurocaudatasp. nov. holotype ♀. A) habitus, dorsal view; B) idem, lateral view; C) idem,ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171540/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 1A–C</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate, elongated, subparallel and slightly sinuous sided, setose medially, with anterior margin convex, lateral margin slightly sinuous and posterior margin convex (
<figureCitation box="[1014,1148,797,822]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[203,1371,197,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[202,1384,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Apex of abdomen of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. holotype ♀ A) Terga 8–10, dorsal view; B) Terga 8–10, subgenital plate and gonapophysis, lateral view; C) Sterna 7–8 (subgenital plate), ventral view; D) scheme of figure C." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171544/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 3C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="596" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,545,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,451,833,858]" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">
<typeStatus box="[199,308,833,858]" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Holotype</typeStatus>
description
</emphasis>
<specimenCount box="[461,483,834,857]" pageId="1" pageNumber="596" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
. 
<emphasis box="[499,560,833,858]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Head</emphasis>
. Light yellow with dark spots (
<figureCitation box="[927,1065,833,858]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1963,1985]" captionTargetBox="[200,1390,208,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[200,1394,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head and tegminae of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. A) holotype head, dorsal view; B) paratype head, lateral view; C) holotype tegminae, dorsolateral view;D) idem." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171542/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 2A–B</figureCitation>
). Frons with a pair of tubercles. Vertex with a pair of V-shaped rows of five tubercles each; coronal sulcus conspicuous (
<figureCitation box="[1165,1257,869,894]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1963,1985]" captionTargetBox="[200,1390,208,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[200,1394,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head and tegminae of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. A) holotype head, dorsal view; B) paratype head, lateral view; C) holotype tegminae, dorsolateral view;D) idem." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171542/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Gena smooth, with horizontal row of three inconspicuous tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[759,848,905,930]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1963,1985]" captionTargetBox="[200,1390,208,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[200,1394,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head and tegminae of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. A) holotype head, dorsal view; B) paratype head, lateral view; C) holotype tegminae, dorsolateral view;D) idem." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171542/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Compound eye yellowish, with brown spots (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1963,1985]" captionTargetBox="[200,1390,208,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[200,1394,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head and tegminae of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. A) holotype head, dorsal view; B) paratype head, lateral view; C) holotype tegminae, dorsolateral view;D) idem." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171542/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 2A–B</figureCitation>
). Clypeus ellipsoid, smooth, white. Labrum inverted “U-shaped”, smooth, light brown. Mandibles smooth, dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[301,392,977,1002]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1963,1985]" captionTargetBox="[200,1390,208,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[200,1394,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head and tegminae of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. A) holotype head, dorsal view; B) paratype head, lateral view; C) holotype tegminae, dorsolateral view;D) idem." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171542/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Mandibular and labial palpi dark brown, setose (
<figureCitation box="[980,1071,977,1002]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1963,1985]" captionTargetBox="[200,1390,208,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[200,1394,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head and tegminae of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. A) holotype head, dorsal view; B) paratype head, lateral view; C) holotype tegminae, dorsolateral view;D) idem." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171542/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Antenna yellowish, with light brown and black spots, setose; scapus with foggy-like black spots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,545,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1049,1074]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Thorax</emphasis>
. Light brown, with yellowish spots, rugose, with several scattered tubercles. Pronotum medially with pair of parallel rows of four tubercles each, with conspicuous mid-longitudinal sulcus (
<figureCitation box="[1183,1277,1085,1110]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,418,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,411,1850]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Isagoras aurocaudatasp. nov. holotype ♀. A) habitus, dorsal view; B) idem, lateral view; C) idem,ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171540/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Mesonotum approximately two times longer than pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[741,838,1121,1146]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,418,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,411,1850]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Isagoras aurocaudatasp. nov. holotype ♀. A) habitus, dorsal view; B) idem, lateral view; C) idem,ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171540/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum semiellipsoid (
<figureCitation box="[1197,1294,1121,1146]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,418,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,411,1850]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Isagoras aurocaudatasp. nov. holotype ♀. A) habitus, dorsal view; B) idem, lateral view; C) idem,ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171540/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Scutellum triangular. Proepimeron rounded. Mesoepisternum widening from anterior margin towards posterior margin, with approximately same length of mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[641,728,1193,1218]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,418,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,411,1850]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Isagoras aurocaudatasp. nov. holotype ♀. A) habitus, dorsal view; B) idem, lateral view; C) idem,ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171540/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Probasisternum trapezoidal (
<figureCitation box="[1073,1161,1193,1218]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,418,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,411,1850]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Isagoras aurocaudatasp. nov. holotype ♀. A) habitus, dorsal view; B) idem, lateral view; C) idem,ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171540/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Mesobasisternum subrectangular. Metasternum fused to abdominal sternum I, with conspicuous longitudinal medial carina, widening towards posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[447,535,1265,1290]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,418,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,411,1850]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Isagoras aurocaudatasp. nov. holotype ♀. A) habitus, dorsal view; B) idem, lateral view; C) idem,ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171540/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Meso and metathoracic furcae conspicuous (
<figureCitation box="[1055,1142,1265,1290]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,418,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,411,1850]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Isagoras aurocaudatasp. nov. holotype ♀. A) habitus, dorsal view; B) idem, lateral view; C) idem,ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171540/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="600" pageId="1" pageNumber="596" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,545,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis box="[199,252,1302,1325]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Legs</emphasis>
. All legs light brown with dark brown and yellowish spots (
<figureCitation box="[962,1100,1301,1326]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,418,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,411,1850]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Isagoras aurocaudatasp. nov. holotype ♀. A) habitus, dorsal view; B) idem, lateral view; C) idem,ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171540/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 1A–C</figureCitation>
). Anterior femur trapezoidal, narrowed near trochanter; dorsally setose, with two conspicuous longitudinal carinae; ventrally smooth; conspicuously sinuous at dorsal and ventral margins (
<figureCitation box="[753,887,1373,1398]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,418,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,411,1850]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Isagoras aurocaudatasp. nov. holotype ♀. A) habitus, dorsal view; B) idem, lateral view; C) idem,ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171540/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 1A–B</figureCitation>
). Anterior tibia similar to femur, but rectangular, without narrowing near trochanter (
<figureCitation box="[548,682,1409,1434]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,418,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,411,1850]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Isagoras aurocaudatasp. nov. holotype ♀. A) habitus, dorsal view; B) idem, lateral view; C) idem,ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171540/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 1A–B</figureCitation>
). Mid and posterior legs setose, with all margins straight, anteriorly smooth, posteriorly with two longitudinal parallel carinae (
<figureCitation box="[809,942,1445,1470]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,418,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,411,1850]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Isagoras aurocaudatasp. nov. holotype ♀. A) habitus, dorsal view; B) idem, lateral view; C) idem,ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171540/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 1A–B</figureCitation>
), with posterior leg approximately 1.5 times longer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,545,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis box="[199,266,1518,1541]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Wings</emphasis>
. Tegmina widened at anterior half, gradually narrowing at posterior half, lanceolate with conspicuous elevated shoulder pad, brown with several light brown transverse veins; with yellowish spot at basal third, from anal margin towards shoulder (
<figureCitation box="[495,629,1589,1614]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1963,1985]" captionTargetBox="[200,1390,208,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[200,1394,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head and tegminae of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. A) holotype head, dorsal view; B) paratype head, lateral view; C) holotype tegminae, dorsolateral view;D) idem." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171542/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 2C–D</figureCitation>
). Posterior wing dark brown, with several scattered white spots and light brown transverse veins; reaching apex of tergum 7 while rested (
<figureCitation box="[876,1009,1625,1650]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,418,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,411,1850]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Isagoras aurocaudatasp. nov. holotype ♀. A) habitus, dorsal view; B) idem, lateral view; C) idem,ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171540/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 1A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,545,2010]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,357]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="597" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis box="[199,305,1661,1686]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Rugose, dark brown with scattered weak yellowish spots from abdominal segment 2–7; abdominal segments 8–11 yellowish dorsally, laterally and ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[871,1015,1697,1722]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,418,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,411,1850]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Isagoras aurocaudatasp. nov. holotype ♀. A) habitus, dorsal view; B) idem, lateral view; C) idem,ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171540/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 1A–B</figureCitation>
). Terga 2–7 rectangular, gradually decreasing in length, approximately 1.5 longer than wide. Terga 6–10 with conspicuous medial longitudinal sinuous carina. Tergum 8 dorsally and laterally rectangular; dorsally approximately 1.3 times longer than wide and laterally 1.5 times longer than high (
<figureCitation box="[559,693,1805,1830]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[203,1371,197,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[202,1384,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Apex of abdomen of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. holotype ♀ A) Terga 8–10, dorsal view; B) Terga 8–10, subgenital plate and gonapophysis, lateral view; C) Sterna 7–8 (subgenital plate), ventral view; D) scheme of figure C." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171544/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 3A–B</figureCitation>
). Tergum 9 dorsally subquadrate, laterally almost 1.3 times higher than long (
<figureCitation box="[274,410,1841,1866]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[203,1371,197,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[202,1384,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Apex of abdomen of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. holotype ♀ A) Terga 8–10, dorsal view; B) Terga 8–10, subgenital plate and gonapophysis, lateral view; C) Sterna 7–8 (subgenital plate), ventral view; D) scheme of figure C." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171544/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 3A–B</figureCitation>
). Tergum 10 dorsally subquadrate, slightly concave emarginated posteriorly, laterally with postero-dorsal margin projected (
<figureCitation box="[526,661,1877,1902]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[203,1371,197,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[202,1384,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Apex of abdomen of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. holotype ♀ A) Terga 8–10, dorsal view; B) Terga 8–10, subgenital plate and gonapophysis, lateral view; C) Sterna 7–8 (subgenital plate), ventral view; D) scheme of figure C." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171544/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 3A–B</figureCitation>
). Cercus cylindrical, short, robust, setose, light brown, with rounded apex (
<figureCitation box="[225,366,1913,1938]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[203,1371,197,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[202,1384,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Apex of abdomen of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. holotype ♀ A) Terga 8–10, dorsal view; B) Terga 8–10, subgenital plate and gonapophysis, lateral view; C) Sterna 7–8 (subgenital plate), ventral view; D) scheme of figure C." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171544/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 3A–B</figureCitation>
). Sterna 2–6 rectangular, approximately 1.5 times longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[1194,1287,1913,1938]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,418,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,411,1850]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Isagoras aurocaudatasp. nov. holotype ♀. A) habitus, dorsal view; B) idem, lateral view; C) idem,ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171540/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Sternum 7 rectangular, rugose, two times longer than wide, with several conspicuous carinae, anterior margin straight, lateral margin conspicuously sinuous at proximal half, posterior margin conspicuously concave (
<figureCitation box="[1162,1297,1985,2010]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[203,1371,197,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[202,1384,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Apex of abdomen of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. holotype ♀ A) Terga 8–10, dorsal view; B) Terga 8–10, subgenital plate and gonapophysis, lateral view; C) Sterna 7–8 (subgenital plate), ventral view; D) scheme of figure C." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171544/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 3C–D</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate (sternum 8) elongated, subparallel and slightly sinuous sided, setose medially, with anterior margin convex, lateral margin slightly sinuous, and posterior margin convex (
<figureCitation box="[874,1002,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[203,1371,197,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[202,1384,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Apex of abdomen of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. holotype ♀ A) Terga 8–10, dorsal view; B) Terga 8–10, subgenital plate and gonapophysis, lateral view; C) Sterna 7–8 (subgenital plate), ventral view; D) scheme of figure C." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171544/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="597">Fig. 3C–D</figureCitation>
). Gonapophysis 8 slender, elongated, setose, subtriangular, with anterior margin straight, lateral margin slightly sinuous at medial third, rounded posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[287,410,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[203,1371,197,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[202,1384,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Apex of abdomen of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. holotype ♀ A) Terga 8–10, dorsal view; B) Terga 8–10, subgenital plate and gonapophysis, lateral view; C) Sterna 7–8 (subgenital plate), ventral view; D) scheme of figure C." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171544/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="597">Fig. 3C–D</figureCitation>
). Gonapophysis 9 sub-trapezoidal, with few setae at posterior margin; posterior margin with elongated, slender, inward curved apex (
<figureCitation box="[617,743,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[203,1371,197,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[202,1384,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Apex of abdomen of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. holotype ♀ A) Terga 8–10, dorsal view; B) Terga 8–10, subgenital plate and gonapophysis, lateral view; C) Sterna 7–8 (subgenital plate), ventral view; D) scheme of figure C." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171544/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="597">Fig. 3C–D</figureCitation>
). Paraproct flat, smooth, broad, with lateral margin sinuous, posterior margin rhomboid (
<figureCitation box="[467,591,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[203,1371,197,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[202,1384,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Apex of abdomen of Isagoras aurocaudata sp. nov. holotype ♀ A) Terga 8–10, dorsal view; B) Terga 8–10, subgenital plate and gonapophysis, lateral view; C) Sterna 7–8 (subgenital plate), ventral view; D) scheme of figure C." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1171544/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="597">Fig. 3C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
